-- Malaysia's CIMB, RHB and MBSB to merge and create mega Islamic bank
-- By Yantoultra Ngui and Al-Zaquan Amer Hamzah
-- Thu Jul 10, 2014 08:15AM EDT
-- None



KUALA LUMPUR, July 10 (Reuters) - Malaysia's second-largest bank CIMB Group Holdings Bhd <CIMB.KL> said on Thursday it plans to merge its business with fourth-biggest lender RHB Capital Bhd <RHBC.KL> and to create a larger Islamic bank with smaller rival Malaysia Building Society Bhd <MBSS.KL>.

Shares in the three lenders were suspended from trade on Thursday pending the announcement.